Good morning everyone. Today I'm going to explain something that happens every time scientists do an experiment. When we measure things, our measurements aren't perfect—they have little errors. And when we use those measurements to calculate something new, those errors affect our final answer. 

I'm going to show you how this works with electricity, using three important concepts: voltage, current, and resistance. And I'll use this animation to show you visually how everything connects.

