QUICK REFERENCE - SYMBOLS YOU USED 📝
======================================

R = Resistance = How much something opposes electrical flow
U = Voltage = The "push" or pressure that makes electricity flow
I = Current = How much electricity is flowing
V = Volts = Unit of measurement for voltage
A = Amperes = Unit of measurement for current
Ω = Ohms = Unit of measurement for resistance
u(R) = Absolute Uncertainty = The error range (±0.22 Ω)
u(R)/R = Relative Uncertainty = The error as a percentage (2.01%)
± = Plus or Minus = Means the range (could be higher or lower)
÷ or / = Division = Divide; U/I means U divided by I

